                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 H 35/17</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Olds</hi>) <hi rend="italic">of a Conversation with the
                        Mexican Ambassador</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Téllez</hi>), <hi rend="italic"
                        >December 13, 1927</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1927-12-13">December 13,
                        1927</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Mexican Ambassador called me on the telephone at two p.m. and said that he
                    had had a long telephone talk with his Minister of Foreign Affairs, and that the
                    position of his Government was as he had stated to me in his oral conversation
                    yesterday; nevertheless his Government did not wish to block the investigation
                    and would be willing to have the Consul General appear voluntarily and in his
                    personal capacity, provided that an arrangement could be made whereby he did not
                    appear under subpoena. I told him that I would take the suggestion under
                    consideration and was hopeful that an arrangement along these lines might be
                    effected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>R[<hi rend="smallcaps">obert</hi>] E. O[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >lds</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
